  "html": "<div class=\"sapere aude\"><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Etymology\">Etymology</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=sapere_aude&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Etymology\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><p>It is from the epithet of a parable, explaining that a fool waits for the stream to stop before crossing, while a wise man forgoes comfort and crosses anyway.\n</p><p>The original use seems to be in <i>Epistle II</i> of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horace\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Horace\">Horace</a>&apos;s <i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epistularum_liber_primus\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Epistularum liber primus\">Epistularum liber primus</a></i><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup>: <i>Dimidium facti qui coepit habet: <b>sapere aude</b></i> (&quot;He who has begun is half done: dare to know!&quot;).\n</p><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Pronunciation\">Pronunciation</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=sapere_aude&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Pronunciation\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><ul><li><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classical_Latin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Classical Latin\">Classical</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet\" title=\"Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet\">IPA</a><sup>(<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_pronunciation\" title=\"Appendix:Latin pronunciation\">key</a>)</sup>: <span class=\"IPA\">/&#x2C8;sa.pe.re &#x2C8;au&#x32F;.de&#x2D0;/</span>, <span class=\"IPA\">[&#x2C8;sa.p&#x25B;.r&#x25B; &#x2C8;au&#x32F;.d&#x32A;e&#x2D0;]</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecclesiastical_Latin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ecclesiastical Latin\">Ecclesiastical</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet\" title=\"Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet\">IPA</a><sup>(<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_pronunciation\" title=\"Appendix:Latin pronunciation\">key</a>)</sup>: <span class=\"IPA\">/&#x2C8;sa.pe.re &#x2C8;au&#x32F;.de/</span>, <span class=\"IPA\">[&#x2C8;sa&#x2D0;.p&#x25B;.r&#x25B; &#x2C8;au&#x32F;.d&#x32A;&#x25B;]</span></li></ul><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Phrase\">Phrase</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=sapere_aude&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Phrase\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><p><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"la\"><a href=\"/wiki/sapio#Latin\" title=\"sapio\">sapere</a> <a href=\"/wiki/audeo#Latin\" title=\"audeo\">aud&#x113;</a></strong>\n</p><ol><li>&quot;<i>Have the courage to think for yourself</i>&quot;</li>\n<li>&quot;<i>Have courage to use your own reason</i>&quot;, in the context of committing to tasks that need to be embarked upon, however unpleasant or awkward.</li></ol><h4><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Usage_notes\">Usage notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=sapere_aude&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Usage notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h4><ul><li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Immanuel_Kant\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Immanuel Kant\">Immanuel Kant</a> described it as the motto of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Age_of_Enlightenment\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Age of Enlightenment\">Enlightenment</a> in his essay &quot;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/What_Is_Enlightenment%3F\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:What Is Enlightenment?\">What Is Enlightenment?</a>&quot;.</li>\n<li>It is a frequently used <a href=\"/wiki/motto\" title=\"motto\">motto</a> for academic institutions.</li></ul><h4><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=sapere_aude&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h4><div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\"> ^ </a> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/horace/epist1.shtml\">Epistularum liber primus from The Latin Library</a>, line 40</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>"
